      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterized with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation results traceable to input characterization documentation.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed, but input probability distributions for hemolysis model constants were assumed uniform without physiological characterization data. Traceability between input distributions and literature sources is incomplete. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples (blood analog batches) characterized for rheological properties; batch-to-batch variability quantified and propagated to validation uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump dataset does not include batch-level rheological characterization of the blood analog. Batch-to-batch variability is unquantified. Factor flagged as epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 1 against required level 4."
    },
